<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go lay an egg • lay an egg</xh5><p> <i>go lay an egg—</i>is used to rudely tell a person to go away (and stop being annoying): “How many times have I told you not to smoke in my....” “Ah, <u>go lay an egg</u>.”</p><p> <i>lay an egg</i>—(sl.) 1. fail completely; give an utterly unsuccessful performance: The play was a failure. They certainly <u>laid an egg</u> this time. 2. drop a bomb: The plane duly <u>laid an egg</u>. I was crouched alongside a wall. The bomb landed on the other side of the wall. 3. <i>(U.S.)</i> laugh very hard: I was so shocked I didn’t know whether to cry or <u>lay an egg</u>.</p> </entry>
